field_body.value:
A former dry cleaning operation at 401 Hall St. SE released hazardous chemicals including tetrachloroethylene, or PCE, and trichloroethylene, or TCE. They belong to a family of chemicals derived from petroleum called volatile organic compounds, or VOCs. PCE and TCE can cause health issues such as headaches and dizziness, and long-term exposure may cause cancer.

VOCs can cause an environmental problem called vapor intrusion. The PCE and TCE in the soil and groundwater may release vapors that move up through the ground and can sometimes seep into properties through poorly sealed basements causing indoor air pollution.
